vgmstream (2083-1foundry4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * No source changes — re-issue of 1foundry3 after fixing the CI build
    environment. 1foundry3 was supposed to pick up 26.04's ffmpeg 8 /
    libavcodec62, but publish.yml builds .debs on the GitHub-hosted
    noble (24.04) runner, not in ubuntu:26.04 — so dpkg-shlibdeps still
    pinned to libavcodec60. publish.yml now wraps `scripts/build-all.sh`
    in `docker run ubuntu:26.04`, which is the only base we support.
    ${shlibs:Depends} re-resolves to libavcodec62 / libavformat62 /
    libavutil60 as confirmed by a local rebuild on 2026-05-20.

 -- Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>  Wed, 20 May 2026 03:41:13 +0000

vgmstream (2083-1foundry3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Rebuild against Ubuntu 26.04's ffmpeg 8 / libavcodec62. The earlier
    ffmpeg-6 sonames (libavcodec60, libavformat60, libavutil58) were
    SRU'd out of 26.04 since 1foundry2 was built on 2026-05-18, leaving
    foundry-linux-retro-tools unresolvable on freshly-pulled 26.04
    boxes. Caught by foundry-linux-setup/test/test-retro-tools-e2e.sh.
    No source changes — ${shlibs:Depends} auto-resolves to the new
    sonames at build time. (1foundry3 turned out to be a no-op because
    CI was still building on noble — see 1foundry4 above.)

 -- Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>  Wed, 20 May 2026 03:19:21 +0000

vgmstream (2083-1foundry2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Enable G.722.1 (Siren 14) codec — it is compiled from plain C source
    in src/coding/libs/ (not a vendored Windows binary), and the upstream
    enables it by default. Disabling it was incorrect and would silently
    break decoding of files using coding_G7221C.
  * Add pkg-config to Build-Depends (required by cmake's find_package).
  * Correct package description: ATRAC9/CELT/G.719 are disabled because
    their decoders are Windows-only DLLs; G.722.1 is now correctly listed
    as enabled.

 -- Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>  Mon, 18 May 2026 18:00:00 +0000

